Question 1¶

  • There seems to be a correlation between rain fall and housing prices, there are hardly counties that have an average home price above 200,000 that have over an average daily rain fall of over .2".
  • There also seems to be the same kind of relationship between average wind speed and home value. Very few counties with and median home price over 200,000 had an average wind speed over 15 mph.
  • There is much less of a correlation between temperature and house value, there does seem to be a slight upper limit of around 50 degrees for the average temperature.
  • There was no observable correlation between humidity and house value.
